  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 7018.2 sitting right between the max positive gamma wall at 7000 (9.9B) and max negative gamma at 7015 (-1.8B), dealers are caught in a narrow hedging zone where they're likely mixed - some selling the bounce above 7015 while others prepare to buy any dip back toward 7000. The PIN regime with massive positive gamma walls stacked above (7050, 7100) creates a strong ceiling effect that should cap upside momentum and attract profit-taking. Key inflection points are the 7000 support wall where dealer buying should emerge and the 7050 resistance where selling pressure intensifies.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to get pinned between 7000-7050 with limited upside due to heavy dealer selling pressure above.",
